data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider let you opt in to sync-over-async with `EnableSyncOverAsync()`. **In .NET 11 that opt-in is removed entirely.** Every synchronous LINQ operator (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now throws `InvalidOperationException` at runtime — there is no configuration workaround.

## Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
| Sync (breaks) | Async (replacement) |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `SaveChangesAsync()` |

All async LINQ methods require `using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`.

**Callers must also go async** — `async`/`await` propagates up the call stack, so controller actions, service methods, etc. that call these repository methods need updating too.
